<h3>INDIAN RENAISSANCE&nbsp;</h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The socio intellectual revolution that took place in the nineteenth century in the fields of philosophy, literature, science, politics and social reforms is often known as Indian Renaissance.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Intellectual criteria of social reform in Indian case = Rationality + religious universalism</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>E.G. OF ACTIVITIES UNDER INDIAN RENAISSANCE&nbsp;</h3>
<ol>
<li>Religious reforms were necessary for social reforms.</li>
<li>RRR = rationality for judging social relevance of any custom/ritual. =&gt; Replace faith with rationality&nbsp;</li>
<li>Brahmo Samaj = repudiation of infallibility of vedas&nbsp;</li>
<li>Socio cultural movement against = backward element of traditional culture in terms of both religious and social evils</li></ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>CHANGES MADE DURING RENAISSANCE =&gt;&nbsp;</h3>
<ol>
<li>new way of studying Indian past was brought in.</li>
<li>Reinterpretation of Indian religious text and rituals&nbsp;</li>
<li>new movement for socio-religious reforms&nbsp; - RRR</li>
<li>Rise to study of English literature thoughts, philosophies and books of history</li></ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>OTHER FACTORS THAT ACCELERATED INDIAN RENAISSANCE.</h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>presence of Colonial government, Economic and Social backwardness of society, influence of modern western ideas, rise of intellectual awakening in the middle class and poor position of women in society</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>LIMITATIONS OF INDIAN RENAISSANCE.&nbsp;</h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ol>
<li>not reach mass peasantry and urban poor,&nbsp;</li>
<li>inadequate force on composite culture and technological reforms, music art science</li>
<li>broadly focussed on religious and social aspect =&gt; not complete renaissance</li></ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Conclusion&nbsp;</h3>
<p>These reform movements stood for the democratization of the society, removal of superstitions and decadent customs, spread of enlightenment and development of a rational and modern outlook. This led to the national awakening in India.</p>